# DIBS Business Portal - Product Requirements Document

## 1. Introduction

### 1.1 Purpose
This document outlines the product requirements for the DIBS Business Portal, a platform designed for small to mid-size real estate businesses to manage their teams, track coaching activities, and handle administrative functions.

### 1.2 Scope
The DIBS Business Portal MVP focuses on essential features for real estate business owners and managers with a single office location, with emphasis on team management, coaching, and core business operations.

### 1.3 Target Users
- Real estate brokerage owners
- Office/team managers
- Training directors
- Administrative staff

## 2. Core Features

### 2.1 Dashboard & Overview
- **Priority: High**
- A centralized dashboard showing critical business metrics and alerts:
  - Agent activity summary
  - Coaching session completion rates
  - Performance metrics at a glance
  - Upcoming training deadlines
  - Business alerts (billing, compliance issues)

### 2.2 Team Management

#### 2.2.1 Agent Directory
- **Priority: High**
- Comprehensive view of all agents/employees including:
  - Contact information
  - License information and expiration dates
  - Role and specialization
  - Performance tier
  - Hire date
  - Profile photo

#### 2.2.2 Role Management
- **Priority: Medium**
- Define system access roles and permissions
- Assign agents to teams or specializations

### 2.3 Coaching & Development

#### 2.3.1 Coaching Sessions
- **Priority: High**
- Schedule and track one-on-one coaching sessions
- Log session notes, action items, and follow-ups
- Review historical coaching data
- Track coaching frequency and completion

#### 2.3.2 Training Programs
- **Priority: High**
- Assign required training (new agent onboarding, continuing education)
- Track completion of mandated real estate certifications
- Create custom training paths for different agent roles
- Monitor progress and send reminders

#### 2.3.3 Mentorship Program
- **Priority: Medium**
- Match experienced agents with newer team members
- Define mentorship schedules and milestones
- Track effectiveness of mentorship pairings

### 2.4 Performance & Goals

#### 2.4.1 Goal Setting & Tracking
- **Priority: High**
- Create and monitor agent performance goals:
  - Listings taken
  - Sales closed
  - Revenue generated
  - Client acquisition
  - Activities completed (calls, meetings, open houses)
- Visualize progress toward goals

#### 2.4.2 Transaction Pipeline
- **Priority: Medium**
- Track deals in progress across the team
- Identify bottlenecks in the sales process
- Monitor conversion rates

#### 2.4.3 Agent Development Plans
- **Priority: Medium**
- Create individualized growth plans
- Track skill development over time
- Align plans with business objectives

### 2.5 Business Administration

#### 2.5.1 Business Profile
- **Priority: High**
- Configure company information
- Upload logo and branding elements
- Set business hours and contact details

#### 2.5.2 User Management
- **Priority: High**
- Add, remove, and deactivate user accounts
- Set permissions based on roles
- Manage access to sensitive information

#### 2.5.3 Billing & Subscription
- **Priority: High**
- Manage subscription plan
- Update payment methods
- View invoices and payment history
- Adjust seat count

#### 2.5.4 Commission Structure
- **Priority: Medium**
- Define default commission splits
- Create performance-based incentive structures
- Set up transaction fee calculations

### 2.6 Analytics

#### 2.6.1 Performance Metrics
- **Priority: High**
- Agent productivity reports
- Team performance comparisons
- Activity vs. results correlation

#### 2.6.2 Coaching Effectiveness
- **Priority: Medium**
- Measure impact of coaching on performance
- Track before/after metrics for training programs
- Calculate ROI on coaching investment

#### 2.6.3 Business Health
- **Priority: Medium**
- Revenue trends
- Agent retention rates
- Cost per transaction

## 3. Technical Requirements

### 3.1 User Interface
- Mobile-responsive design for all core functions
- Intuitive navigation optimized for daily use
- Clear data visualization with actionable insights
- Consistent UI patterns across all modules

### 3.2 Performance
- Dashboard load time under 3 seconds
- Data updates at minimum every 15 minutes
- Support for concurrent users (10+ for small businesses)

### 3.3 Security
- Role-based access controls
- Data encryption for sensitive information
- Compliance with real estate industry regulations
- Regular security audits

### 3.4 Integration
- Calendar integration for scheduling (Google, Outlook)
- Email notifications for alerts and reminders
- CSV export functionality for reports

## 4. User Roles & Permissions

### 4.1 Owner/Broker
- Full access to all features and data
- Administrative control of permissions
- Financial reporting and billing management

### 4.2 Office Manager
- Team management capabilities
- Limited administrative functions
- Performance reporting access
- Training and coaching tools

### 4.3 Team Lead
- Access limited to assigned team members
- Coaching and goal-setting tools
- Performance metrics for direct reports

### 4.4 Agent
- Personal dashboard with individual metrics
- Access to own coaching sessions and notes
- Training module access
- Goal progress visibility

## 5. Future Considerations (Out of MVP Scope)

### 5.1 Expansion Features
- Multiple office/location management
- Advanced market analytics
- Automated coaching recommendations
- Integration with MLS and transaction management systems
- Client relationship management
- Marketing campaign tracking
- Recruiting and hiring pipeline
- Advanced compensation management

## 6. Success Metrics

### 6.1 Product Adoption
- 80%+ agent login rate weekly
- 90%+ of scheduled coaching sessions completed
- All agents with active goals and development plans

### 6.2 Business Impact
- Measurable improvement in agent productivity
- Reduction in agent turnover
- Increased coaching effectiveness
- Time savings for administrative tasks

## 7. Implementation Timeline

### 7.1 MVP Timeline
- Phase 1: Core Dashboard, Team Management, User Access (4 weeks)
- Phase 2: Coaching Tools, Performance Goals (4 weeks)
- Phase 3: Analytics, Business Administration (4 weeks)
- Beta Testing: 2 weeks with select customers
- Full Release: 2 weeks post-beta for adjustments

## 8. Appendix

### 8.1 Real Estate Specific Considerations
- License renewal tracking and alerts
- Industry compliance requirements
- Standard transaction workflow stages
- Common real estate performance metrics

### 8.2 Glossary
- **Coaching Session**: Structured one-on-one meeting between manager and agent
- **Development Plan**: Customized growth roadmap for individual agents
- **Transaction Pipeline**: Visual representation of deals in progress
- **Commission Split**: Revenue sharing arrangement between agent and brokerage 